node.text:
Quick easy glam for any occasion... 

So today I wanted to show you a quick easy make up look that can basically be used for any occasion a day at the office, date night, even a chilled Sunday family lunch.

I also wanted to do a tutorial that allows people to create this look using the make up they have right now!

I generally like to start of with applying mascara and eyeliner which are my two favorites and I feel like I’ve set a basis for my look. I’ve been using the Essence volumn stylist mascara and the long lasting eyeliner as well. These are my staples and youll literally never catch me without these!

Next I go in with my foundation which is the L’Oréal True Match in the shade Honey. Its important to find a “pliable” foundation that works with your skin. Because a lot of the foundations can end up looking cakey.

Next I went in with a little bit of the Mac Pro longwear concealer which also assists in highlighting  and illuminates the area.

For the eyeshadow I chose a wintry rusty colour and applied that to my entire eyelid. Just to add a little bit of sparkle I added a bronze glitter but only to the centre part of my eyelid.

And then we highligh?... I applied the Essence highlighter in the shade 10 Heroic to my cheek bones the tip of my nose and chin and a little of my forehead as well..

Last but not least to complete the look, some lipstick ?. I used the Wet n Wild lipstick ,in the shade Bare it all! This had definitely become my go to favorite lipstick!

node.text:
Lockdown started on 15th March, 2020 and we never saw it coming, Nor did we know or still know when is it going to end.

The never-seen-before uncertainty and the standstill, the danger and the calm, the silence yet the screams of pain from the people affected. Nothing has changed yet so much has changed. For some, their life is never going to be the same. For some it is just a hard time that'll pass.

So much has happened, subconsciously, but nothing has happened to our notice. 
But I think the most challenging thing that has translated through the string of months of lockdown, is that previously in the near past, we were all looking for a "riddance".

A riddance emotionally, the strenuous to-do list was probably an escape we chose to ignore the things wrong with us, and around us.

The lessons extracted are that somehow we never cared enough for people around, and hardly emoted where it matters.

Atleast I won't take the actual-valued things for granted,
I look at the silver lining out of the dark clouds this pandemic brought. I hope you do too with a silent prayer that everything gets back to normal but we don't forget these months and the changes they brought InshaAllah ????
